description:
Ryan Lanciaux
http://nodevember.org/talk/Ryan%20Lanciaux
You have an idea and quickly write some code to bring this idea to life. You share the code online and somehow people find and actually start using this module you wrote. Now what?

In this talk we will discuss some things to do and things to avoid when managing a personal, open-source library. Additionally, we'll explore some ways that everyone, open-source contributor or not, can help promote a healthy and vibrant ecosystem.
title: Personal Open Source in the age of JavaScript fatigue
